Clustering

- unsupervised learning task of separating data into groups by similarity
- used for exploratory analysis, subgrouping, improve predictive models
- we standardize to see differences
- cluster based on type/ classification

1. choose K (number of centroids)
2. randomly place centroids
3. assign observations to the closest centroid
4. centroid of each cluster calculated based on all observations of the cluster
5. adjust the observations based on the newly moved centroid + loop step 3 and 4 until nothing is moving/ reassigned

- good cluster is tightly packed around centroid, has small within cluster sum of squared distance (WSSD)
    - WSSD: add squared distance between each point and center(mean) of cluster
